# MuJoCo MCP - Cursor Configuration

## Project Overview
MuJoCo MCP enables AI agents to control MuJoCo physics simulations through the Model Context Protocol.

## Key Features
- Natural language control of physics simulations
- Real-time visualization with MuJoCo viewer
- Support for various robot models and scenes
- Full MCP standard compliance

## Available MCP Tools
- `get_server_info` - Get server information
- `create_scene` - Create physics simulations
- `step_simulation` - Advance simulation time
- `get_state` - Get current simulation state
- `set_joint_positions` - Control joint angles
- `reset_simulation` - Reset to initial state
- `close_viewer` - Close viewer window

## Code Guidelines
1. Keep code simple and readable
2. Follow PEP 8 style guide
3. Add docstrings to all functions
4. Use type hints where possible
5. Test all new features

